ğŸ”¹ What is a View?

A View is a virtual table based on a query.

It does not store data, only the query definition in MySQLâ€™s data dictionary.

Data is fetched from the underlying base tables at query time.

ğŸ“Œ Example:

CREATE VIEW emp_dept_view AS
SELECT e.emp_name, d.dept_name, e.salary
FROM employees e
JOIN department d ON e.dept_id = d.dept_id;

ğŸ”¹ Where is a View Stored?

Only the definition (SQL query) is stored in information_schema.VIEWS.

No actual data is stored.

Check definition:

SHOW CREATE VIEW emp_dept_view;

ğŸ”¹ Types of Views

Simple View â†’ Based on one table, no joins/aggregates.

CREATE VIEW emp_salary_view AS
SELECT emp_name, salary FROM employees;


Complex View â†’ Based on multiple tables or joins.

CREATE VIEW emp_dept_view AS
SELECT e.emp_name, d.dept_name FROM employees e JOIN department d ON e.dept_id = d.dept_id;


Aggregate (Non-updatable) View â†’ Uses GROUP BY, SUM, AVG, etc.

CREATE VIEW avg_salary_view AS
SELECT dept_id, AVG(salary) AS avg_salary FROM employees GROUP BY dept_id;


Updatable View â†’ Allows INSERT/UPDATE/DELETE if rules are followed.

CREATE VIEW emp_update_view AS
SELECT emp_id, emp_name, salary FROM employees;

ğŸ”¹ Updatable vs Non-Updatable Views
Feature	Updatable View	Non-Updatable View
Based on	Single table, simple SELECT	Joins, Aggregates, GROUP BY, etc.
Can update data?	âœ… Yes (INSERT, UPDATE, DELETE allowed)	âŒ No (read-only)
Example	SELECT emp_id, emp_name, salary	SELECT dept_id, AVG(salary)

ğŸ“Œ Example of update via updatable view:

UPDATE emp_update_view
SET salary = 65000
WHERE emp_id = 101;


âŒ Example of non-updatable:

UPDATE avg_salary_view
SET avg_salary = 80000
WHERE dept_id = 1;
-- ERROR: The target view is not updatable

ğŸ”¹ Advantages of Views

Security â†’ restrict column/row access.

Simplification â†’ hide complex joins.

Data abstraction â†’ hide table structure.

Reusability â†’ predefined queries.

ğŸ”¹ Disadvantages of Views

Performance overhead (query runs every time).

Some views are not updatable.

If base table changes (dropped/modified), view may break.

Cannot index views (only base tables).

ğŸ”¹ Materialized Views in MySQL

âŒ Not supported natively in MySQL.

âœ… Can be simulated using tables + refresh logic.

ğŸ“Œ Example (simulated materialized view for avg salary):

CREATE TABLE mv_avg_salary AS
SELECT dept_id, AVG(salary) AS avg_salary
FROM employees
GROUP BY dept_id;

-- Refresh manually
TRUNCATE TABLE mv_avg_salary;
INSERT INTO mv_avg_salary
SELECT dept_id, AVG(salary) FROM employees GROUP BY dept_id;


Or refresh automatically with events:

CREATE EVENT refresh_mv_avg_salary
ON SCHEDULE EVERY 1 HOUR
DO
  REPLACE INTO mv_avg_salary
  SELECT dept_id, AVG(salary) FROM employees GROUP BY dept_id;

